With major football competitions suspended and players ordered to remain at home due to Covid-19, the continent’s stars have found a way to keep fit. African stars, including Nigeria captain, Ahmed Musa, Lille’s Victor Osimhen, Al Ahly winger, Ramadan Sobhi, have joined their colleagues in taking the Stay at Home challenge as they observe self-isolation to contain the spread of coronavirus. The Stay at Home challenge involves players juggling toilet rolls instead of footballs in their houses. While the world continues to battle the coronavirus pandemic that has seen training sessions, several leagues and continental competitions suspended, footballers embarked on the challenge to keep in good shape.